This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
EXT Code #1
Bail jumping on Waukesha County case 21CF47.

10:50 AM; Case called for Intitial appearance. Defendant Delon J White in court.  Zachary A Wittchow appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty. Dorlack appeared as a friend of the court.  Atty. Dorlack does not know why the defendant has failed to appear.  Court will issue a warrant, cash bail $1500.00.
Initial appearance on May 6, 2022 at 10:30 am.

10:53 AM; Case called for Initial appearance.   Defendant Delon J White not in court.  Kristi J Gordon appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty. Dorlack, who represents the defendant in 21CF47, notes he was not aware of this new case and does not represent the defendant in this matter.  Atty. Dorlack advises the court that the defendant contacted him to advise that he cannot appear for court this morning, but could appear this afternoon.  Court advises that due to other matters it cannot hear this matter this afternoon.  Court will issue a capias in 21CF47 but not issue a warrant in this matter.  Court will continue to tag this matter along with 21CF47 for status.  Check Case scheduled for April 22, 2022.
